OL,3,CUK's oldest cinema, The Electric,
OL,4,Ccloses after 114 years
OL,6,FThe cinema, built on a converted taxi
OL,7,Frank, showed its first silent movie on
OL,8,F27 December 1909 and is believed to be
OL,9,Fthe oldest working cinema in the UK.
OL,11,FIt has two digital screens and showed
OL,12,Fa mixture of mainstream, independent,
OL,13,Fforeign and classic films.
OL,15,FIt has been through several names
OL,16,Fincluding Select Cinema, Tatler News
OL,17,FTheatre, The Jacey and The Classic and
OL,18,FThe Tivoli before becoming The
OL,19,FElectric again in 1993.
